orest. There was no France outside the door, of course. Those mincing movements … Sunny nonsense.

“No, it’s not complicated at all,” the seaman was saying, “here’s how it works—you have an iron bucket and a coal pit. You start scraping. Lightly at first, so long as the coal goes sliding down into the bucket by itself, then you scrape harder. When you’ve filled the bucket you set it on a cart. You roll it over to the chief stoker. A bang of his shovel and—one!—the firebox doo